        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3557275502" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1911726334463927738">This was such a sweet story. Kelsey was a like able character who had a strong sense of responsibility. When her family is on the verge of ruin she steps up and does the only thing she thinks is left for her to do. She sells herself at auction to be a mistress of one of the Lords if the ton. <br/><br/>Derek is not interested in having a mistress, he’s not interested in marriage either. But he can’t in good conscience let the girl he sees on the auction block be auctioned to the cruel man who is winning th</span>
  <span id="freeText1911726334463927738" style="display:none">This was such a sweet story. Kelsey was a like able character who had a strong sense of responsibility. When her family is on the verge of ruin she steps up and does the only thing she thinks is left for her to do. She sells herself at auction to be a mistress of one of the Lords if the ton. <br /><br />Derek is not interested in having a mistress, he’s not interested in marriage either. But he can’t in good conscience let the girl he sees on the auction block be auctioned to the cruel man who is winning the bidding. So he steps in and wins her. <br /><br />But in reality Kelsey wins him over with her sweet temperament and her intelligent conversation. Soon Derek doesn’t ever want to be a part from her.<br /><br />I loved all of this. But I would have loved it so much bette if the narrator wouldn’t have made Derek, and all of the men in the story for that matter, sound so uppity. The way he spoke for them made them all sound old and it killed Derek’s sex appeal. <br /><br />So I enjoyed the story, but I just wasn’t attracted to the Hero the way I should have been.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1911726334463927738" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

