<span id="freeTextContainer15787622507818974332">Interesting read and well paced. You won’t be disappointed to have read it! :) I enjoyed the unique plot, and although the villain in the story was disgusting and horrible, it kept me glued to the book. <br/><br/>I think my greatest problem with this book is that it’s trajectory went on a very different course than I was expecting based off of the description. I was expecting more angst and heartbreak, but the H cared and loved h very easily. <br/><br/>Also, there’s a lot of Malory family drama and updates in this </span>
  <span id="freeText15787622507818974332" style="display:none">Interesting read and well paced. You won’t be disappointed to have read it! :) I enjoyed the unique plot, and although the villain in the story was disgusting and horrible, it kept me glued to the book. <br /><br />I think my greatest problem with this book is that it’s trajectory went on a very different course than I was expecting based off of the description. I was expecting more angst and heartbreak, but the H cared and loved h very easily. <br /><br />Also, there’s a lot of Malory family drama and updates in this book. As someone who was reading this as a stand-alone, it was very annoying to read about 20 other characters constantly who hold no significance to you. I couldn’t even keep straight who was who. But I imagine if you read the whole series and like all these characters, this could be a bonus. I had to skim through some of it.</span>
