<div id="review_4047856503" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4047856503" />
    <a title="Jessica Reads It" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/46739531-jessica-reads-it"><img alt="Jessica Reads It" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1623720913p2/46739531.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4047856503?book_show_action=true">Jun 08, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jessica Reads It" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jessica Reads It" href="/user/show/46739531-jessica-reads-it">Jessica Reads It</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780783819273" href="/book/show/6651821-say-you-love-me">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/46739531-jessica-reads-it?shelf=historical-romance">historical-romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/46739531-jessica-reads-it?shelf=realistic-fiction">realistic-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/46739531-jessica-reads-it?shelf=womens-fiction">womens-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/46739531-jessica-reads-it?shelf=2021-reads">2021-reads</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/46739531-jessica-reads-it?shelf=book-series">book-series</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/46739531-jessica-reads-it?shelf=romance">romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/46739531-jessica-reads-it?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/46739531-jessica-reads-it?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/46739531-jessica-reads-it?shelf=family-drama">family-drama</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/46739531-jessica-reads-it?shelf=regency-romance">regency-romance</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4047856503" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3498116476040349585">I adored “𝘚𝘢𝘺 𝘠𝘰𝘶 𝘓𝘰𝘷𝘦 𝘔𝘦” and all the free advice on being a mistress (I actually think a lot of those are still applicable but let me know what you think in the comments) 😀⁣<br/>⁣⁣<br/>Kelsey Langton has lost her parents in an incident dubbed, “𝘛𝘩𝘦 𝘛𝘳𝘢𝘨𝘦𝘥𝘺” and she and her sister are forced to seek refuge at her aunts. Due to her uncle&apos;s gambling problems they are in debt and seeks to save her remaining family the only way young women at the time can- by selling herself as a mistress⁣⁣<br/>⁣⁣<br/>Kelsey is such a</span>
  <span id="freeText3498116476040349585" style="display:none">I adored “𝘚𝘢𝘺 𝘠𝘰𝘶 𝘓𝘰𝘷𝘦 𝘔𝘦” and all the free advice on being a mistress (I actually think a lot of those are still applicable but let me know what you think in the comments) 😀⁣<br />⁣⁣<br />Kelsey Langton has lost her parents in an incident dubbed, “𝘛𝘩𝘦 𝘛𝘳𝘢𝘨𝘦𝘥𝘺” and she and her sister are forced to seek refuge at her aunts. Due to her uncle's gambling problems they are in debt and seeks to save her remaining family the only way young women at the time can- by selling herself as a mistress⁣⁣<br />⁣⁣<br />Kelsey is such a contradiction- naive and sweet at the beginning but with a hidden depth and desire brewing. ⁣⁣Derek Malory bids on the sweet temptress but has no idea she is a proper lady and not a woman of the night. ⁣⁣<br />⁣⁣<br />Their story was comical and watching the characters navigate this unfortunate situation, especially in social circumstances had me rolling in tears. ⁣⁣I like how the author incorporated their story into the overall Malory family plotline. I’ve never seen such a distinguished and prestigious family with more “bodies” in their closet and constantly lashed with scandals. ⁣⁣<br />⁣<br />𝐀𝐝𝐯𝐢𝐜𝐞 𝐨𝐧 𝐛𝐞𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐚 𝐦𝐢𝐬𝐭𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐬: ⁣⁣<br />⁣⁣<br />🔥 In the business of being a mistress, one must keep it as impersonal as possible⁣⁣<br />⁣⁣<br />🔥 A mistress must provide what the man does not get from home⁣⁣<br />⁣⁣<br />🔥Never lay there like a wet blanket. Caress him at every opportunity when you are alone. Make him think you want him constantly, whether you do or don’t.⁣⁣<br />⁣⁣<br />🔥By far the most important piece of advice of all being a mistress as do not fall in love⁣⁣<br /><br />I can't wait to read more Malory family drama! </span>
  <a data-text-id="3498116476040349585" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


